cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with camera relocalisation, which is a problem in computer vision related to simultaneous localisation and mapping, virtual/augmented reality, and navigation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method for adapting pre-trained regression forests to new scenes on the fly, which involves machine learning techniques such as regression and decision trees. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.RO (Robotics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.GR (Graphics).
